  "description": "¶What Agda is Agda is a dependently typed functional programming language based on Martin-Löf type theory. It is simultaneously a programming language and a proof assistant: every well-typed program is a proof, and every proof is a program.\nUnlike Lean, which provides a tactic language for constructing proofs interactively, Agda proofs are written as ordinary function definitions using pattern matching. There is no tactic layer — the proof IS the code. This design choice makes proofs explicit and readable at the cost of less automation.\n",
